@timberland is debuting the Archive Gallery at Paris Fashion Week Men's 2026. Alongside Sami Taider of The Archivist Store, you can take a deep dive into some of the most enduring pieces of the brand's collection, demonstrating the breadth of garments that form the foundation of where workwear and contemporary menswear intersect. ⁠
⁠
If you're in Paris, be sure to check it out before it's gone: the space is only open to the public on Thursday, June 25th of June at Timberland Le Marais on 14 Rue du Temple. Hit the link in our bio to learn more.

